rned about the birds and the bees when I was younger, your just a prime example of how evolution skipped over you. How's it feel to live a life as just a boy, never more? Muhaha, grow up child and remember, next time you tell someone to do something, once again think before you type and speak, your brain and your hands are just digging you deeper and deeper into that hole you created for yourself. <br><br>You see simply put, you act like a kindergardener. You see all they do is call each other names but how often do they physically fight. Synide, I won't engage in a name calling dispute anymore, I enjoy sitting back letting you make a fool out of yourself and if I telling it like it is, angers you? Well guess what, name a time when I ever gave a shit about what you thought or what anyone else here thought about me when I came out and addressed a problem, it's often those who sound the alarms that get criticized, trouble is, I don't really care what you think about me, let me sing you a song or rehearse this rhyme. Sticks and stones may break my bones but names will never harm me. Think about that next time you try to provoke me into another kindergarden name calling session.<br><br>I do admit, some days I am in the mood for a good debate and what better place to do it on then a EQ board. Right now is almost one of those times Synide, long day at work, come home sit down, have dinner then see a simple minded post such as yours. Really, I do sometimes think they should rename this board to Drinals Comedy Hour. Some of the fighting I see that goes on over a game is just to much to bear, to see adults who behave worse then a 2 year old. Mind you many do not here, but there are the select few and I must admit sometimes I tear into people, but when you step back and look at the big picture I often laughed and said, all that for a game? <br><br>Oh I have to laugh when I log on and I get a tell and people say HEY what's up, and I reply with a hello how are you? How did you know I was on. There reply usually is, ohh someone said it over guildchat, I have to laugh at least I did one thing, i've been a major impact on a community, some may like me some may not, I am not here to please everyone nor will I ever begin to try. It's about me taking that 989 each month and getting the most out of it. That's what counts. To the person who said I am the cause for the world gone bad? LoL, really, now tell me did you document that to? I am the cause to plague and famine, that's pretty funny, I never did read that entire post, I couldn't help but roll over and laugh so hard. I was almost begging for more, I printed that out and took that into work and put it up outside my office door and made sure everyone read it, it was sort of the memo of the day. It was truly amusing, then when a employee asked me where it came from, I explained that was from a game and someones description of me. She looked at me and began to laugh, as did I. Of course I had to shrug first. Take it for its face value and by all means happy flaming, but at least try to be grown up about it. Though I admit sometimes it's easy to sink to the lvl's of certain people here. *glares at Synides name, just to name one out of the dozens here*<br><br>I can't put Balrak there since I was speaking out of context from a role playing state and character.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFFF><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub28.ezboard.com/ulukasz.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lukasz</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://images.honesty.com/imagedata/h/920/07/29200752.jpg BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 215<br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/21/01 6:08:24 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub28.ezboard.com/fdrinal28133frm12.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=166.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Flaming, poetic or chi